# Frontend Architecture

The LocalCA frontend is built with Next.js and uses a modern React architecture with Tailwind CSS for styling.

## Key Components

- [app/](mdc:app) - Next.js app directory (App Router)
  - [page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Main dashboard page
  - [layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout component
  - [create/](mdc:app/create) - Certificate creation pages
  - [certificates/](mdc:app/certificates) - Certificate management pages
  - [settings/](mdc:app/settings) - Settings pages
- [components/](mdc:components) - Reusable React components
  - [ui/](mdc:components/ui) - UI components (buttons, cards, etc.)
- [data/](mdc:data) - Data fetching and state management
  - [ca/](mdc:data/ca) - CA-related data operations
  - [service/](mdc:data/service) - Service API clients
- [hooks/](mdc:hooks) - Custom React hooks
- [styles/](mdc:styles) - Global styles and theme configuration

## Technologies

- Next.js - React framework
- React - UI library
- Tailwind CSS - Styling
- Radix UI - Accessible component primitives
- React Hook Form - Form handling
- Zod - Schema validation

